parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty heater core can cause overheating, coolant leaks, and steam to enter the vehicle, posing a risk to driver and passenger safety.
symptoms: steam entering the vehicle through vents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine overheating can cause damage to the engine, coolant leaks, and steam to enter the vehicle, posing a risk to driver and passenger safety.
A faulty head gasket can cause oil leaks, engine damage, and carbon monoxide to enter the passenger compartment, posing a risk to driver and passenger safety.
symptoms: carbon monoxide entering the passenger compartment.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A broken timing belt can cause engine damage, stalling, and potentially lead to accidents.
Failed motor mounts can cause engine vibration, noise, and potentially lead to engine damage.

The failure of the electrical system can cause various malfunctions, including power window failure, ignition switch issues, and transmission problems, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded. In severe cases, it can even cause engine compartment fires, resulting in significant damage and safety risks.
symptoms: passenger side passive seat belt malfunction
automatic transmission intermittently fails to shift into 4th gear

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to malfunction, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded. In some cases, it may require the driver to turn the key off and on to reset the transmission, which can be a safety risk.
symptoms: Transmission intermittently fails to shift into 4th gear
transmission flies back into 3rd gear when on the freeway

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the CV joint can cause the vehicle to malfunction, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
The failure of the axle can cause the vehicle to malfunction, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Long axle metal donut outside diamond press
pressed on shaft from the differential
slid down and wedged in the front wheel axle pivot.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Passenger Side Automatic Seat Belt Retractor Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the passenger side automatic seat belt retractor can cause the seat belt to become stuck or loose, leading to inadequate restraint in the event of an accident, which can increase the risk of injury or death.
symptoms: The passenger side seat belt does not lock in place
becomes loose from the top retractor
and will not retract or release the shoulder belt.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the heater core can cause hot coolant and steam to fill the interior of the vehicle, obstructing the driver's vision, and potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: filling the interior of the car with hot coolant and steam
and creating a hot and uncomfortable environment.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unrelated Issue: Front Passenger Window Malfunction
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the front passenger window can cause inconvenience and discomfort to the passenger.
symptoms: The front passenger window comes down when the passenger door is closed.
